GulfTalent.com
Dynamics AX - Technical Analyst
Emirates Leisure Retail (ELR)
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 6 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
The AX Technical Analyst will provide company-wide strategic, analytical, and technical support for the AX ERP system. The AX Technical Analyst will actively manage, customise and support the business applications. Analyse and provide technical solutions for business customizations and system improvements. Acts as an intermediary between the business community and the AX functional business analysts working with IT project teams and business clients to collect, clarify, and translate business requirements into business applications. The AX technical analyst is heavily involved in the maintenance of the ERP systems and configurations.
REQUIREMENTS
• At least 4-5 years of experience writing code in X++, MorphX, SSRS, SSAS, and relational databases
• Hands on experience in customizations/enhancements in Dynamics AX 2009/ AX 2012 modules including Financial/Inventory /Purchasing/Sales/ Master Planning, including managing user accounts & security profiles
• Experience with 2-4 full life cycle of Dynamics AX implementations
• Hands on experience in debugging code and unit testing written code base.
• Develop functional and technical specifications for Microsoft Dynamics AX 2009/ AX 2012 enhancements and integrations to other business applications. Partners with stakeholders, process specialists, and users to elicit and document business requirements
• Breaking down functional requirements into technical designs, development tasks and executing to completion.
• Translate non-technical requirements into technical business requirements. Have an understanding of overall architecture. Design and review Technical design documents
• Administer & manage overall technical performance of the AX system. Install and manage development, test/UAT and production environments. Performs on-going monitoring and refinement of AX 2009/ AX 2012 customizations
• Assist in defect closing, defect tracking and defect root cause analysis. Assist in doing Unit, system and integration testing. Formulate deployment strategies.
• Install and manage development, test/UAT and production environments. Evaluates alternate solutions and design processes and systems which includes user impact considerations,
• Uses current knowledge of business and technology to recommend systems and process improvements
• Critically evaluates information gathered from multiple sources, reconciles conflicts, abstracts up from low-level information to a general understanding, and works with customers to uncover unmet business needs
ABOUT THE COMPANY
Emirates Leisure Retail is a fully fledged division of the high profile Emirates Group, with strong interests in establishing, managing and franchising a wide ranging portfolio of restaurants, cafés, bars and lounges in the Gulf Cooperative Council countries and far beyond.
Headquartered in Dubai, in the United Arab Emirates, ELR’s operations span the adjoining emirates of Abu Dhabi, Sharjah, Ajman and Ras Al Khaimah, the city of Muscat in the Sultanate of Oman and most recently Australia.
ELR is part of the MMI group, which over the course of 100 years has created vested businesses in trade, travel, IT, corporate services, leisure retail and liquor. In 2007 the leisure operations of the group were divested to create a new limited liability company, rebranded as Emirates Leisure Retail.
